<section xmlns="https://code.dccouncil.us/schemas/dc-library" xmlns:codified="https://code.dccouncil.us/schemas/codified" xmlns:codify="https://code.dccouncil.us/schemas/codify" xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude" containing-doc="D.C. Code">
  <num>31-1809</num>
  <heading>Examination authority.</heading>
  <para>
    <num>(a)</num>
    <text>A reinsurance intermediary shall be subject to examination by the Mayor. The Mayor shall have access to all books, bank accounts, and records of the reinsurance intermediary in a form usable to the Mayor.</text>
  </para>
  <para>
    <num>(b)</num>
    <text>A reinsurance manager may be examined as if it were the reinsurer.</text>
  </para>
  <annotations>
    <annotation doc="D.C. Law 10-47" type="History" path="§10">Oct. 21, 1993, D.C. Law 10-47, § 10, 40 DCR 6093</annotation>
